messages.message: @Kathy Wu is there any update on where this might be coming from? I tried a new app on UAT and now see the same lack of provenance tracking as on PROD.

from this doc (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1G8IoycYUum_YFNyIvSHtukoaLPRco2ivgGPklEQYVKg/edit) it seems like aihub-uat.internal is our main uat environment that we deploy to, whereas aihub.uat only has manual deploys so it might be out of date-- that could be why the envs are different. i'm not sure if there have been changes to provenance recently on the model side, @Rafal would you know?

Thanks @Kathy Wu and @Serena, yesterday I build the applications live with the customer on aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com), it had no provenance tracking anywhere. I just rebuild the application on aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com (http://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com), provenance tracking is a lot better here (it catches 90% of the fields in a first test)
